The following code provides a function to transform the data of application mass to get an inversely scaled line representing the mass applied in grams per week.

app_inv_line <- function(
    dates_sim = get("dates_sim", envir = .GlobalEnv), 
    substance = get("substance", envir = .GlobalEnv), 
    Application_all_c = get("Application_all_c", envir = .GlobalEnv), 
    GKB1_mon_all_d = get("GKB1_mon_all_d", envir = .GlobalEnv), 
    GKB2_mon_all_d = get("GKB2_mon_all_d", envir = .GlobalEnv), 
    substance_list = get("substance_list", envir = .GlobalEnv),
    max_y = NULL  # New parameter for max_y
) {
  if (is.null(dates_sim) || is.null(substance) || is.null(Application_all_c) || is.null(GKB1_mon_all_d) || is.null(substance_list)) {
    stop("Please provide all required arguments: dates_sim, substance, Application_all_c, GKB1_mon_all_d, and substance_list.")
  }
  
  # Generate the week sequence
  week_sequence <- seq(floor_date(min(dates_sim), "week"), 
                       ceiling_date(max(dates_sim), "week"), 
                       by = "week")
  
  # Filter applications based on the substance
  if (substance == substance_list[3]) {
    # rep(0,...) to re(NA,...) ====
    filtered_app <- data.frame(Week = as.POSIXct(dates_sim), mass_ai = rep(NA, length(dates_sim)))
  } else {
    filtered_app <- Application_all_c %>%
      filter(active_ingredient == substance) %>%
      mutate(Date = as.Date(Date)) %>%  # Ensure the Date is in Date format
      group_by(Week = floor_date(Date, "week")) %>%  # Group by week
      summarise(mass_ai = sum(`a.i. used (in g)`), .groups = 'drop') %>%
      mutate(Week = as.POSIXct(Week))  # Extract mass applied
  }
  
  # Create complete filtered application data
  df_mass <- tibble(Week = week_sequence) %>%
    left_join(filtered_app, by = "Week") %>%
    mutate(mass_ai = replace_na(mass_ai, 0)) %>%
    mutate(mass_ai = mass_ai/1000)
  
  # Calculate the maximum y-value for GKB1
  max_y_gkb1 <- max(GKB1_mon_all_d[[substance]], na.rm = TRUE)
  
  # Calculate the maximum y-value for GKB2 if provided
  max_y_gkb2 <- if (!is.null(GKB2_mon_all_d)) {
    max(GKB2_mon_all_d[[substance]], na.rm = TRUE)
  } else {
    0  # Default to 0 if GKB2 data is not provided
  }
  
  # If max_y is not provided, calculate it
  if (is.null(max_y)) {
    max_y <- max(max_y_gkb1, max_y_gkb2)
  }
  
  max_mass <- max(filtered_app$mass_ai, na.rm = TRUE)
  
  # Calculate scale factor
  scale_f <- ifelse(max_mass == 0, 0, (max_y / 2) / max_mass)
  
  return(list(df_mass = df_mass, scale_f = scale_f, max_y = max_y))
}

str_to_num = function(x) {
  cleaned_string <- str_remove_all(x, "[^0-9.]")  # Remove non-numeric characters except decimal points
  as.numeric(cleaned_string)  # Convert to numeric
}

clean_conc <- function(dataset, columns) {
  dataset %>%
    mutate(across(all_of(columns), 
                  ~ case_when(
                    grepl("< LOD", .) ~ as.numeric(
                      lodloq_2010[1, cur_column()] / 2),
                    grepl("< LOQ", .) ~ as.numeric(
                      (lodloq_2010[1, cur_column()] + lodloq_2010[2, cur_column()]) / 2),
                    grepl("no sample", ., ignore.case = TRUE) ~ NA_real_,
                    TRUE ~ as.numeric(.)
                  )))
}

# Add time to datetime
time_decoding <- function(dataset) {
  dataset %>% mutate(time = case_when(time_of_day == "Q1" ~ "03:00:00",
                                      time_of_day == "Q2" ~ "09:00:00",
                                      time_of_day == "Q3" ~ "15:00:00",
                                      time_of_day == "Q4" ~ "21:00:00",
                                      time_of_day == "AM" ~ "06:00:00",
                                      time_of_day == "PM" ~ "18:00:00")) %>%
              mutate(datetime = as.POSIXct(paste(date, time)))
}

GKB1_mon_2010_d = time_decoding(GKB1_mon_2010_c)
GKB1_mon_2011_d = time_decoding(GKB1_mon_2011_c)
GKB2_mon_2010_d = time_decoding(GKB2_mon_2010_c)
GKB2_mon_2011_d = time_decoding(GKB2_mon_2011_c)

Following code provides a function to read the data of simulations from the csv files in the data folder.

# Simulation Data
read_csv_files <- function(folder_path) {
  # List all CSV files in the folder
  csv_files <- list.files(folder_path, pattern = "\\.csv$", full.names = TRUE)
  
  # Read each CSV file and store it in a list with the file name as the key
  data_list <- lapply(csv_files, function(file) {
    # Get the file name without the extension
    file_name <- tools::file_path_sans_ext(basename(file))
    # Read the CSV file
    data <- read.csv(file, header = TRUE, sep = ",")
    # Assign the data frame to the list with the file name as the key
    setNames(list(data), file_name)
  })
  
  # Combine all data frames into a single list
  data_list <- do.call(c, data_list)
  return(data_list)
}
read_csv_from_folders <- function(parent_folder) {
  # List all folders in the parent directory
  folders <- list.dirs(parent_folder, full.names = TRUE, recursive = FALSE)
  print(folders)
  # Initialize an empty list to store data frames
  all_data <- list()
  
  # Loop through each folder and read CSV files
  for (folder in folders) {
    folder_name <- basename(folder)  # Get the folder name
    all_data[[folder_name]] <- read_csv_files(folder)  # Read CSV files and store in the list
  }
  
  return(all_data)
}

# Count applications of each active ingredient that do not share OBJECTID and Date with another ingredient
unique_applications <- Application_all_c %>%
  group_by(Date, OBJECTID) %>%
  summarise(active_ingredients = list(unique(active_ingredient)), .groups = 'drop') %>%
  mutate(num_ingredients = sapply(active_ingredients, length)) %>%
  filter(num_ingredients == 1) %>%  # Keep only groups with a single ingredient
  unnest(active_ingredients) %>%
  group_by(active_ingredients) %>%
  summarise(count = n(), .groups = 'drop')

# Create pairs of active ingredients for each application
pairs_df <- Application_all_c %>%
  group_by(Date, OBJECTID) %>%
  summarise(active_ingredients = list(unique(active_ingredient)), .groups = 'drop') %>%
  filter(length(active_ingredients) > 1) %>%  # Keep only groups with more than one ingredient
  mutate(pairs = lapply(active_ingredients, function(x) {
    if (length(x) > 1) {
      combn(x, 2, simplify = FALSE)
    } else {
      NULL
    }
  })) %>%
  unnest(pairs)

# Create a data frame for edges
edges <- pairs_df %>%
  mutate(from = sapply(pairs, `[`, 1),
         to = sapply(pairs, `[`, 2)) %>%
  group_by(from, to) %>%
  summarise(count = n(), .groups = 'drop')

all_active_ingredients <- unique(c(edges$from, edges$to, unique_applications$active_ingredients))


# Create a data frame for nodes
nodes <- data.frame(name = all_active_ingredients) %>%
  left_join(unique_applications, by = c("name" = "active_ingredients")) %>%
  mutate(count = ifelse(is.na(count), 0, count))

# Create a graph object
g <- graph_from_data_frame(edges, directed = FALSE, vertices = nodes)

# Plot the network graph with edge size based on count and node size based on unique applications
ggraph(g, layout = "fr", niter = 1600) +
  geom_edge_link(aes(edge_alpha = count, width = count)) +
  geom_node_point(aes(size = count), color = "steelblue") +  # Nodes sized by unique applications
  geom_node_text(aes(label = name), repel = TRUE) +
  labs(title = "Netzwerk der Applikationsmischungen",
       edge_width = "Anzahl Ko-Applikationen",
       size = "Anzahl Einzel-Applikationen") +
  theme_void() +
  scale_edge_width(range = c(0.5, 2)) +  # Adjust the edge width range as needed

plots <- lapply(substance_list, function(substance) {
  week_sequence <- seq(
    floor_date(min(dates_sim), "week"), 
    ceiling_date(max(dates_sim), "week"), 
    by = "week"
  )
  
  filtered_app <- if (substance == substance_list[3]) {
    data.frame(Week = as.POSIXct(dates_sim), mass_ai = rep(0, length(dates_sim)))
  } else {
    Application_all_c %>%
      filter(active_ingredient == substance) %>%
      mutate(Date = as.Date(Date)) %>%
      group_by(Week = floor_date(Date, "week")) %>%
      summarise(mass_ai = sum(mass_ai_kg), .groups = 'drop') %>%
      mutate(Week = as.POSIXct(Week))
  }
  
  filtered_app_complete <- tibble(Week = week_sequence) %>%
    left_join(filtered_app, by = "Week") %>%
    mutate(mass_ai = replace_na(mass_ai, 0))
  
  max_y <- max(
    max(GKB1_mon_all_d[[substance]], na.rm = TRUE), 
    max(GKB2_mon_all_d[[substance]], na.rm = TRUE)
  ) * 1.2
  
  max_mass <- max(filtered_app$mass_ai, na.rm = TRUE)
  scale_f <- ifelse(max_mass == 0, 0, (max_y / 2) / max_mass)
  
  substance_title <- substance_abbr[which(substance == substance_list)]
  
  base_plot <- ggplot() +
    geom_line(data = GKB1_mon_all_d, aes(x = as_datetime(datetime), y = !!sym(substance)),
              color = "#1F77B4FF") +
    geom_line(data = GKB2_mon_all_d, aes(x = as_datetime(datetime), y = !!sym(substance)),
              color = "#FF7F0EFF") +
    scale_x_datetime(limits=as_datetime(c("2010-03-01 00:00:00","2011-12-31 00:00:00"))) +
    scale_y_continuous(breaks = scales::breaks_extended(n = 5),
                       labels = scales::label_number(accuracy = 0.1)) +
    labs(title = substance_title) +
    theme_classic() +
    theme(legend.position = "none", 
          axis.title.x = element_blank(), 
          axis.title.y = element_blank())
  
  if (substance_title == "FOE-SA") {
    plot <- base_plot +
      scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = sec_axis(~ ., name = "Applizierte Masse", 
                                             breaks = 0, labels = "00"),
                         breaks = scales::breaks_extended(n = 5),
                         labels = scales::label_number(accuracy = 0.1)) +
      theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10), 
            axis.text.y.right = element_text(color="white"))
  } else {
    plot <- base_plot +
      geom_line(data = filtered_app_complete, aes(x = Week, y = max_y - scale_f * mass_ai),
                color = "#2CA02CFF") +
      scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = sec_axis(~ (max_y - .) / scale_f, name = "Applizierte Masse"),
                         breaks = scales::breaks_extended(n = 5),
                         labels = scales::label_number(accuracy = 0.1))
    if (which(substance == substance_list) <= 9) {
      plot <- plot + theme(axis.text.x = element_blank())
    } else {
      plot <- plot + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, angle = 30, hjust = 1))
    }
    
    plot <- plot + theme(axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10))
  }
  
  return(plot)
})

substance_mon_cor = GKB1_mon_all_d %>%
  select(Flufenacet,Diflufenican,`S-Metolachlor`,date) %>%
  as.data.frame()
colnames(substance_mon_cor) = c("FFA","DFF","MTS","date")
substance_mon_cor$date = as_date(substance_mon_cor$date)



merged_data <- merge(substance_mon_cor, weather_vars, by = "date")  
weather_vars <- c("TEMPERATURE_AVG", "PRECIPITATION", "WINDSPEED", "VAPOURPRESSURE", "ET0")
cor_results <- data.frame(Substance = character(), Variable = character(), Correlation = numeric(), P_Value = numeric(), stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# List of substances
substances <- c("FFA", "MTS", "DFF")

# Loop through each substance
for (substance in substances) {
  for (var in weather_vars) {
    # Perform correlation test
    test_result <- cor.test(merged_data[[substance]], merged_data[[var]], use = "complete.obs")
    
    # Store the results in cor_results
    cor_results <- rbind(cor_results, data.frame(Substance = substance, Variable = var, Correlation = test_result$estimate, P_Value = test_result$p.value))
  }
}

# Print the final results
print(cor_results)

acf_plots <- list()

for (var in weather_vars) {
  acf_plot <- acf(weather[[var]], main = paste("ACF of", var), plot = FALSE)
  acf_df <- data.frame(Lag = acf_plot$lag, ACF = acf_plot$acf)
  i <- which(var == names(weather_vars)[-6])
  p <- ggplot(acf_df, aes(x = Lag, y = ACF)) +
    geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed", color = "red") +
    labs(title = var_titles[i], x = "Lag", y = "ACF") +
    theme_minimal()
  acf_plots[[var]] <- p
}

file = "C:/Users/morit/Desktop/MA/xAquaticRisk-Analysis/data/Gw80Dr100/Flu Gw80Dr100/arr.dat"
dat_retrieve = function(file,dataset) {
  data_read <- h5read(file = file, name = dataset)
  dim_data <- dim(data_read)
  h5readAttributes(file,dataset)
  n_timestep <- dim_data[2]
  # Create a data.frame to store daily deposition sums.
  dep_timestep <- data.frame(
    time_day = 1:n_timestep,
    deposition = rep(NA, n_timestep)
  )
  
  # Loop over each day to calculate total deposition
  # (Only summing non-zero values; adjust the unit conversion factor as needed.)
  for (i in 1:n_timestep) {
    # Extract the spatial matrix for day i
    timestep_matrix <- data_read[,i]
    # Convert to vector and sum non-zero (and non-NA) values
    timestep_sum <- sum(timestep_matrix[timestep_matrix != 0], na.rm = TRUE)
    dep_timestep$deposition[i] <- timestep_sum
  }
  return(dep_timestep)
}

ffa_mon_peaks <- flu_mon %>%

first_order_kinetics <- function(time_vector, initial_concentration, dt50) {
  k <- log(2) / dt50
  concentration <- initial_concentration * exp(-k * time_vector)
  return(concentration)
}

dt50 = 5.3
init_date = as_date("2010-05-25")
init_conc = 10
datetime_seq <- seq(from = init_date, by = "days", length.out = 365)
time <- as.numeric(difftime(datetime_seq, init_date, units = "days"))
concentration_values <- first_order_kinetics(time, init_conc, dt50)
dt50_line <- data.frame(DateTime = datetime_seq, Concentration = concentration_values)

init_date2 = as_date("2010-07-03")
init_conc2 = 4.03
datetime_seq2 <- seq(from = init_date2, by = "days", length.out = 365)
time2 <- as.numeric(difftime(datetime_seq2, init_date2, units = "days"))
concentration_values2 <- first_order_kinetics( time2, init_conc2, dt50)
dt50_line2 <- data.frame(DateTime = datetime_seq2, Concentration = concentration_values2)
